Bharti Enterprises to Sell Stake in Comviva, Dow Jones Reports

-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 
2011-03-24T09:25:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/bharti-enterprises-to-sell-stake-in-comviva-dow-jones-reports.html
Bharti Enterprises Ltd. plans to
sell a controlling stake in Comviva Technologies Ltd., its
mobile software development unit, Dow Jones reported, citing
three people familiar with the matter.  The valuation for the firm would have to be at least $300
million to $400 million, the news service said.  Bharti has already offered to sell Comviva to two possible
buyers, Dow Jones said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Kraus at 
 jkraus2@bloomberg.net  